Package: mpshock
Title: Monetary Policy Shock Series for Empirical Macroeconomics
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Charles", "Coverdale", email = "charlesfcoverdale@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: Provides a curated collection of monetary policy shock and
    stance series from the empirical macroeconomics literature, bundled as
    tidy data frames with provenance metadata. Version 0.1.0 includes
    eight series for the United States: the policy news shock from
    Nakamura and Steinsson (2018) <doi:10.1093/qje/qjy004>, the
    orthogonalised surprise from Bauer and Swanson (2023)
    <doi:10.1257/aer.20200994>, the target and path factors of the
    Swanson (2021) <doi:10.1016/j.jmoneco.2020.09.003> extension of
    Gurkaynak, Sack, and Swanson (2005), the pure monetary policy and
    central bank information shocks from Jarocinski and Karadi (2020)
    <doi:10.1257/mac.20180090>, the informationally-robust shock from
    Miranda-Agrippino and Ricco (2021) <doi:10.1257/mac.20180124>, and
    the shadow federal funds rate of Wu and Xia (2016)
    <doi:10.1111/jmcb.12300>. Helpers support date alignment, frequency
    conversion, and shock cumulation. All data is bundled; no runtime
    network access is required.
